cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper deals with the task of nuclei segmentation in histopathology images using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV). The paper also utilizes a conditional generative adversarial network (cGAN) for nuclei segmentation, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The authors also mention the use of spectral normalization and gradient penalty, which are techniques commonly used in optimization and regularization of deep learning models, and thus the paper could also be classified under Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with histopathology images, which are a type of medical imaging, and thus could also be classified under Multimedia (cs.MM).
